    "ts": "2026-03-20T11:22:47+00:00",
    "headline": "Unilever in talks to sell foods business to U.S.-based buyer",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: Unilever is in talks to sell its foods business to the U.S.-based McCormick & Company.</p><p>A possible deal would bring together Unilever brands like Hellmann's with McCormick's famous Cholula hot sauce.</p><p>Unilever's foods segment made up about a quarter of its total sales last year - which made it just under $15 billion.</p><p>The firm confirmed Friday (March 20) it had received an inbound offer for the business.</p><p>The talks signal a potential speed up of CEO Fernando Fernandez's new strategy.</p><p>He wants to reposition Unilever towards higher-margin beauty and personal care categories.</p><p>The conglomerate already sold-off its ice cream business last year, which included the Magnum brand.</p><p>The companies said in a statement there's no certainty they will agree a deal.</p><p>They also didn't give out financial details.</p><p>Unilever's foods business includes brands like Colman and Marmite.</p></body>",
